
[1]quietism

   QUI'ETISM, n. Peace or tranquility of mind; apathy; dispassion;
   indisturbance; inaction. In history, quietism is the system of the
   quietists, who maintained that religion consists in the internal rest
   or recollection of the mind, employed in contemplating God and
   submitting to his will.
